-- Johnson Leads Australia's Fight Back as England Collapses to 187 All Out
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2010-12-17T07:10:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-17/johnson-leads-australia-s-fight-back-as-england-collapses-to-187-all-out.html
Australia bowled England out for 187
on day two of the third Ashes cricket Test in Perth to take an
81-run first innings lead as it seeks to tie the series.  Recalled fast bowler  Mitchell Johnson  took 6-38 and Ryan
Harris claimed 3-59 as England lost 10 wickets for 109 runs
after reaching 78 without loss. Australia will begin its second
innings after an early tea break was taken.  Ian Bell  top scored for England with 53, while captain
 Andrew Strauss  made 52.  England leads the best-of-five contest 1-0.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  